The paper deals with matrix recovery and denoising, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Gaussian measurements and noise also suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as a possible sub-category. The optimization problems involved in the paper also suggest numerical analysis (cs.NA) as a potential sub-category. Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve matrices belonging to different constraint classes, which could fall under scientific computing (cs.SI).
